# GitHub Workflows & Actions Development Guidelines

## 🎯 Core Principles

1. **GitHub Actions Focus**: All code specific to GitHub Workflows, Actions, and platform features
2. **SRE Mindset**: Reliability, scalability, observability, security, cost optimization
3. **Idempotency**: Consistent results when run multiple times with same inputs
4. **Modularity**: Reusable workflows, composite actions, clear separation of concerns

## 📁 Workflow Structure

```
.github/
├── workflows/
│   ├── ci.yml              # Main CI pipeline (lint, test, security)
│   ├── release.yml         # Release automation (triggered by CI)
│   ├── docker-publish.yml  # Docker build (triggered by Release tags)
│   └── reusable-*.yml      # Reusable workflow templates
├── actions/
│   └── custom-action/      # Composite or JavaScript actions
│       ├── action.yml
│       └── src/
└── CODEOWNERS              # Review requirements
```

## 🔗 Workflow Chaining Pattern

This project uses chained workflows for proper CI/CD:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    🧪 CI Pipeline                           │
│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  │
│  │📝 Commit │  │🐍 Backend│  │⚛️ Frontend│  │🔐 Security  │  │
│  │   Lint   │  │  Tests   │  │  Tests   │  │   Scan     │  │
│  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └─────┬───────┘  │
│       └─────────────┴────────────┴───────────────┘          │
│                           ▼                                 │
│                    ✅ CI Success                            │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
                           │ workflow_run (on success)
                           ▼
              ┌────────────────────────┐
              │     🚀 Release         │
              └───────────┬────────────┘
                          │ push tag (v*)
                          ▼
              ┌────────────────────────┐
              │  🐳 Docker Build       │
              └────────────────────────┘
```

### Chain Implementation

```yaml
# release.yml - Triggers after CI
on:
  workflow_run:
    workflows: ["🧪 CI Pipeline"]
    types: [completed]
    branches: [main, master]

# docker-publish.yml - Triggers on version tags
on:
  push:
    tags:
      - 'v*'
```

